Parliament, Monday, 11 March 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries will tomorrow receive a progress report from the Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries on the implementation of the recommendations of the Harris Nupen Molebatsi and Emang Basadi forensic reports. The committee will receive reports from the Interdepartmetnal Task Team on the implementation of the Food and Nutrition Security Policy and the establishment of the Food Control Agency – and on addressing challenges facing the poultry industry. Also, the committee will receive a report from the Marine Living Resources Fund on the implementation of the Audit Action Plan on issues raised by the Auditor-General. The department will reflect on the Internal Audit Committee’s recommendations on conditional grants. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 12 March 2019
	Time: 9.30 am
	Venue: Committee Room 2, Upper Ground Floor, 90 Plein Street Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE, FORESTRY AND FISHERIES, MS MACHWENE SEMENYA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Klaas Zizipho (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 2311
	Cell: 0783482450
	E-mail: zklaas@parliament.gov.za The Constitution says a parliamentary committee meeting may not be closed to the public “unless it is reasonable and justifiable to do so in an open and democratic society”.Read more